						<summary>

						<p>Fourth pillar in the Rāmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record the gift of land and a perpetual lamp by Sūrapa Nāyaka. Also mentions Koṇḍachamūpati, son of Mummaḍi Bhīma of Haihaya family. In characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
